title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 870 Police Magnum
location: se okc / newalla, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
18" barrel with magazine extension for a 6+1 capacity. Shoots 2 3/4" and 3" shells. It has rifle sights and I polished the bolt while it was out. This is an actual police gun used by a police department that I bought and completely disassembled and refinished. I replaced the synthetic furniture with wingmaster wood but the original set is included with the gun. This gun was made to work and it functions as it should, you will not find a better gun for home defense. I added a list below of some of the major differences between the police and express guns just to give those of you who dont know why the police versions are more desirable.


The 870 Police has:
 - An aluminum trigger group (vs plastic on the 870 express).
 - Old style magazine retention system (you can add mag extension w/o modification) 
 - The Police gun receives a higher level of inspection and finishing and is built in a special area of the plant from 100% inspected parts.
 - A military-grade parkerized finish.
 - A polished bore.
 - A one piece barrel.
 - A short police-length fore end. 
- The Remington “R3” super recoil pad that reduces felt recoil by 30%.
 - Sling swivels.
 - Heavy-duty magazine spring to ensure positive shell feeding.
 - Heavy-duty trigger-sear spring. to reduce the chance of accidental fire
 - Heavy-duty shell lifter spring which also improves positive feeding.
 - No use of MIM parts, the extractor is milled
 - Police shotguns do not have an ISS (Integrated Safety System) which is a locking mechanism on the safety of commercial shotguns. This type of locking mechanism can cause delay to an officer who needs the weapon but does not have the appropriate key. LE shotguns have the standard, proven, cross bolt safety.
- The receivers used in Police guns are “vibra honed” to smooth out rough finishes and remove burrs before parkerization or bluing.
 - High visibility follower.

title: For Sale:  AK-47  AK-74 select fire Drilling Fixture
postcontent:
The fixture is a drilling template made of machined steel that properly places the sear pin hole in the receiver for the auto sear pin. There are machined steel pins that are used to hold the fixture in place on the receiver. There is still a small amount of modification that has to be done to the carrier rail to allow for clearance for the trip in the receiver. Since the pin holes are two different sizes on the opposite sides of the AK-47 receiver a bushing is provided for the right side hole to guide the bit that is the same size as the bit to eliminate the need to center punch this hole.
